tspan.tspan: 1. Select a method for cutpoint
The analyses will separate the samples into
Low/High risk group with this method.
Optimal Cut Point method will maximize the
intra-group difference but will take longer
time. Mean by Default.
1.1 Customize group by Percentile
An alternative method for cut point is by using
percentile. User can use the slide bar to select
the ceiling percentile for "Low" group and floor
percentage for "High" group. Percentiles in
between (shown as grey) are omitted. Both
values are 50% by default.
2. Overall Survival or Event Free Survival
For datasets from TARGET project, event-free
survival (EFS) are supported. Option for EFS is
disabled when non-TARGET datasets are
selected.
3. Signature Sets to be Compared
Signature cell type composition in datasets
are inferred through CIBERSOFT. The
correlation between high/low group separation
and signature cell types will be calculated.
4. Review All Inputs
The analysis can start after
reviewing all the inputs.
Whether to only use samples with p<0.05 in
signature cell type estimation.
